  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The King\u2019s Banquets"
      title: "The King\u2019s Banquets"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now in the days of Ahasuerus, the Ahasuerus who reigned from India
        to Ethiopia over 127 provinces, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'in those days when King Ahasuerus sat on his royal throne in Susa,
        the citadel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'in the third year of his reign he gave a feast for all his officials
        and servants. The army of Persia and Media and the nobles and governors of
        the provinces were before him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'while he showed the riches of his royal glory and the splendor and
        pomp of his greatness for many days, 180 days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And when these days were completed, the king gave for all the people
        present in Susa the citadel, both great and small, a feast lasting for seven
        days in the court of the garden of the king\u2019s palace. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'There were white cotton curtains and violet hangings fastened with
        cords of fine linen and purple to silver rods[[COMMENT(0)]] and marble pillars,
        and also couches of gold and silver on a mosaic pavement of porphyry, marble,
        mother-of-pearl, and precious stones. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Drinks were served in golden vessels, vessels of different kinds,
        and the royal wine was lavished according to the bounty of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And drinking was according to this edict: \u201CThere is no compulsion.\u201D
        For the king had given orders to all the staff of his palace to do as each
        man desired. "
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Queen Vashti\u2019s Refusal"
      title: "Queen Vashti\u2019s Refusal"
      number: 9
      content: 'Queen Vashti also gave a feast for the women in the palace that belonged
        to King Ahasuerus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'On the seventh day, when the heart of the king was merry with wine,
        he commanded Mehuman, Biztha, Harbona, Bigtha and Abagtha, Zethar and Carkas,
        the seven eunuchs who served in the presence of King Ahasuerus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'to bring Queen Vashti before the king with her royal crown,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        in order to show the peoples and the princes her beauty, for she was lovely
        to look at. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But Queen Vashti refused to come at the king\u2019s command delivered
        by the eunuchs. At this the king became enraged, and his anger burned within
        him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the king said to the wise men who knew the times (for this was
        the king\u2019s procedure toward all who were versed in law and judgment, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "the men next to him being Carshena, Shethar, Admatha, Tarshish, Meres,
        Marsena, and Memucan, the seven princes of Persia and Media, who saw the
        king\u2019s face, and sat first in the kingdom): "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAccording to the law, what is to be done to Queen Vashti, because
        she has not performed the command of King Ahasuerus delivered by the eunuchs?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Memucan said in the presence of the king and the officials,
        \u201CNot only against the king has Queen Vashti done wrong, but also against
        all the officials and all the peoples who are in all the provinces of King
        Ahasuerus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For the queen\u2019s behavior will be made known to all women, causing
        them to look at their husbands with contempt,[[COMMENT(0)]] since they will
        say, \u2018King Ahasuerus commanded Queen Vashti to be brought before him,
        and she did not come.\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '1:17 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "This very day the noble women of Persia and Media who have heard
        of the queen\u2019s behavior will say the same to all the king\u2019s officials,
        and there will be contempt and wrath in plenty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'If it please the king, let a royal order go out from him, and let
        it be written among the laws of the Persians and the Medes so that it may
        not be repealed, that Vashti is never again to come before King Ahasuerus.
        And let the king give her royal position to another who is better than she. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So when the decree made by the king is proclaimed throughout all
        his kingdom, for it is vast, all women will give honor to their husbands,
        high and low alike.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'This advice pleased the king and the princes, and the king did as
        Memucan proposed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: He sent letters to all the royal provinces, to every province in its
        own script and to every people in its own language, that every man be master
        in his own household and speak according to the language of his people.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Esther Chosen Queen'
      title: Esther Chosen Queen
      number: 1
      content: '  After these things, when the anger of King Ahasuerus had abated,
        he remembered Vashti and what she had done and what had been decreed against
        her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then the king\u2019s young men who attended him said, \u201CLet beautiful
        young virgins be sought out for the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And let the king appoint officers in all the provinces of his kingdom
        to gather all the beautiful young virgins to the harem in Susa the citadel,
        under custody of Hegai, the king\u2019s eunuch, who is in charge of the women.
        Let their cosmetics be given them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And let the young woman who pleases the king[[COMMENT(0)]] be queen
        instead of Vashti.\u201D This pleased the king, and he did so.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now there was a Jew in Susa the citadel whose name was Mordecai,
        the son of Jair, son of Shimei, son of Kish, a Benjaminite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'who had been carried away from Jerusalem among the captives carried
        away with Jeconiah king of Judah, whom Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon had
        carried away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He was bringing up Hadassah, that is Esther, the daughter of his
        uncle, for she had neither father nor mother. The young woman had a beautiful
        figure and was lovely to look at, and when her father and her mother died,
        Mordecai took her as his own daughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So when the king\u2019s order and his edict were proclaimed, and
        when many young women were gathered in Susa the citadel in custody of Hegai,
        Esther also was taken into the king\u2019s palace and put in custody of Hegai,
        who had charge of the women. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the young woman pleased him and won his favor. And he quickly
        provided her with her cosmetics and her portion of food, and with seven chosen
        young women from the king\u2019s palace, and advanced her and her young women
        to the best place in the harem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Esther had not made known her people or kindred, for Mordecai had
        commanded her not to make it known. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And every day Mordecai walked in front of the court of the harem
        to learn how Esther was and what was happening to her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now when the turn came for each young woman to go in to King Ahasuerus,
        after being twelve months under the regulations for the women, since this
        was the regular period of their beautifying, six months with oil of myrrh
        and six months with spices and ointments for women\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "when the young woman went in to the king in this way, she was given
        whatever she desired to take with her from the harem to the king\u2019s palace. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "In the evening she would go in, and in the morning she would return
        to the second harem in custody of Shaashgaz, the king\u2019s eunuch, who
        was in charge of the concubines. She would not go in to the king again, unless
        the king delighted in her and she was summoned by name.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When the turn came for Esther the daughter of Abihail the uncle of
        Mordecai, who had taken her as his own daughter, to go in to the king, she
        asked for nothing except what Hegai the king\u2019s eunuch, who had charge
        of the women, advised. Now Esther was winning favor in the eyes of all who
        saw her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And when Esther was taken to King Ahasuerus, into his royal palace,
        in the tenth month, which is the month of Tebeth, in the seventh year of
        his reign, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the king loved Esther more than all the women, and she won grace
        and favor in his sight more than all the virgins, so that he set the royal
        crown[[COMMENT(0)]] on her head and made her queen instead of Vashti. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:17 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '18: Mordecai Discovers a Plot'
      title: Mordecai Discovers a Plot
      number: 18
      content: "Then the king gave a great feast for all his officials and servants;
        it was Esther\u2019s feast. He also granted a remission of taxes to the provinces
        and gave gifts with royal generosity.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now when the virgins were gathered together the second time, Mordecai
        was sitting at the king\u2019s gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Esther had not made known her kindred or her people, as Mordecai
        had commanded her, for Esther obeyed Mordecai just as when she was brought
        up by him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "In those days, as Mordecai was sitting at the king\u2019s gate, Bigthan
        and Teresh, two of the king\u2019s eunuchs, who guarded the threshold, became
        angry and sought to lay hands on King Ahasuerus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And this came to the knowledge of Mordecai, and he told it to Queen
        Esther, and Esther told the king in the name of Mordecai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: When the affair was investigated and found to be so, the men were
        both hanged on the gallows.[[COMMENT(0)]] And it was recorded in the book
        of the chronicles in the presence of the king.
      comments:
      - number: '2:23 '
        content: Or or ; Hebrew or . This Persian execution practice involved affixing
          or impaling a person on a stake or pole (compare Ezra 6:11)
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Haman Plots Against the Jews'
      title: Haman Plots Against the Jews
      number: 1
      content: '  After these things King Ahasuerus promoted Haman the Agagite, the
        son of Hammedatha, and advanced him and set his throne above all the officials
        who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And all the king\u2019s servants who were at the king\u2019s gate
        bowed down and paid homage to Haman, for the king had so commanded concerning
        him. But Mordecai did not bow down or pay homage. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the king\u2019s servants who were at the king\u2019s gate said
        to Mordecai, \u201CWhy do you transgress the king\u2019s command?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And when they spoke to him day after day and he would not listen
        to them, they told Haman, in order to see whether Mordecai\u2019s words would
        stand, for he had told them that he was a Jew. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when Haman saw that Mordecai did not bow down or pay homage to
        him, Haman was filled with fury. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But he disdained[[COMMENT(0)]] to lay hands on Mordecai alone. So,
        as they had made known to him the people of Mordecai, Haman sought to destroy
        all the Jews, the people of Mordecai, throughout the whole kingdom of Ahasuerus.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In the first month, which is the month of Nisan, in the twelfth year
        of King Ahasuerus, they cast Pur (that is, they cast lots) before Haman day
        after day; and they cast it month after month till the twelfth month, which
        is the month of Adar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Haman said to King Ahasuerus, \u201CThere is a certain people
        scattered abroad and dispersed among the peoples in all the provinces of
        your kingdom. Their laws are different from those of every other people,
        and they do not keep the king\u2019s laws, so that it is not to the king\u2019s
        profit to tolerate them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If it please the king, let it be decreed that they be destroyed,
        and I will pay 10,000 talents[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver into the hands of those
        who have charge of the king\u2019s business, that they may put it into the
        king\u2019s treasuries.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        content: A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilograms
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the king took his signet ring from his hand and gave it to Haman
        the Agagite, the son of Hammedatha, the enemy of the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the king said to Haman, \u201CThe money is given to you, the
        people also, to do with them as it seems good to you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  Then the king\u2019s scribes were summoned on the thirteenth day
        of the first month, and an edict, according to all that Haman commanded,
        was written to the king\u2019s satraps and to the governors over all the
        provinces and to the officials of all the peoples, to every province in its
        own script and every people in its own language. It was written in the name
        of King Ahasuerus and sealed with the king\u2019s signet ring. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Letters were sent by couriers to all the king\u2019s provinces with
        instruction to destroy, to kill, and to annihilate all Jews, young and old,
        women and children, in one day, the thirteenth day of the twelfth month,
        which is the month of Adar, and to plunder their goods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'A copy of the document was to be issued as a decree in every province
        by proclamation to all the peoples to be ready for that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The couriers went out hurriedly by order of the king, and the decree
        was issued in Susa the citadel. And the king and Haman sat down to drink,
        but the city of Susa was thrown into confusion.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Esther Agrees to Help the Jews'
      title: Esther Agrees to Help the Jews
      number: 1
      content: '  When Mordecai learned all that had been done, Mordecai tore his
        clothes and put on sackcloth and ashes, and went out into the midst of the
        city, and he cried out with a loud and bitter cry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He went up to the entrance of the king\u2019s gate, for no one was
        allowed to enter the king\u2019s gate clothed in sackcloth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And in every province, wherever the king\u2019s command and his decree
        reached, there was great mourning among the Jews, with fasting and weeping
        and lamenting, and many of them lay in sackcloth and ashes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When Esther\u2019s young women and her eunuchs came and told her,
        the queen was deeply distressed. She sent garments to clothe Mordecai, so
        that he might take off his sackcloth, but he would not accept them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Esther called for Hathach, one of the king\u2019s eunuchs, who
        had been appointed to attend her, and ordered him to go to Mordecai to learn
        what this was and why it was. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Hathach went out to Mordecai in the open square of the city in front
        of the king\u2019s gate, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and Mordecai told him all that had happened to him, and the exact
        sum of money that Haman had promised to pay into the king\u2019s treasuries
        for the destruction of the Jews. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Mordecai also gave him a copy of the written decree issued in Susa
        for their destruction,[[COMMENT(0)]] that he might show it to Esther and
        explain it to her and command her to go to the king to beg his favor and
        plead with him on behalf of her people. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:8 '
        content: 'Or Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Hathach went and told Esther what Mordecai had said. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Esther spoke to Hathach and commanded him to go to Mordecai
        and say, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAll the king\u2019s servants and the people of the king\u2019s
        provinces know that if any man or woman goes to the king inside the inner
        court without being called, there is but one law\u2014to be put to death,
        except the one to whom the king holds out the golden scepter so that he may
        live. But as for me, I have not been called to come in to the king these
        thirty days.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they told Mordecai what Esther had said. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Mordecai told them to reply to Esther, \u201CDo not think to
        yourself that in the king\u2019s palace you will escape any more than all
        the other Jews. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For if you keep silent at this time, relief and deliverance will
        rise for the Jews from another place, but you and your father\u2019s house
        will perish. And who knows whether you have not come to the kingdom for such
        a time as this?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Esther told them to reply to Mordecai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CGo, gather all the Jews to be found in Susa, and hold a fast
        on my behalf, and do not eat or drink for three days, night or day. I and
        my young women will also fast as you do. Then I will go to the king, though
        it is against the law, and if I perish, I perish.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Mordecai then went away and did everything as Esther had ordered him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Esther Prepares a Banquet'
      title: Esther Prepares a Banquet
      number: 1
      content: "    On the third day Esther put on her royal robes and stood in the
        inner court of the king\u2019s palace, in front of the king\u2019s quarters,
        while the king was sitting on his royal throne inside the throne room opposite
        the entrance to the palace. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And when the king saw Queen Esther standing in the court, she won
        favor in his sight, and he held out to Esther the golden scepter that was
        in his hand. Then Esther approached and touched the tip of the scepter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the king said to her, \u201CWhat is it, Queen Esther? What is
        your request? It shall be given you, even to the half of my kingdom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Esther said, \u201CIf it please the king,[[COMMENT(0)]] let the
        king and Haman come today to a feast that I have prepared for the king.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '5:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CBring Haman quickly, so that we may do
        as Esther has asked.\u201D So the king and Haman came to the feast that Esther
        had prepared. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And as they were drinking wine after the feast, the king said to
        Esther, \u201CWhat is your wish? It shall be granted you. And what is your
        request? Even to the half of my kingdom, it shall be fulfilled.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Esther answered, \u201CMy wish and my request is: "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Haman Plans to Hang Mordecai'
      title: Haman Plans to Hang Mordecai
      number: 8
      content: "If I have found favor in the sight of the king, and if it please
        the king[[COMMENT(0)]] to grant my wish and fulfill my request, let the king
        and Haman come to the feast that I will prepare for them, and tomorrow I
        will do as the king has said.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Haman went out that day joyful and glad of heart. But when Haman
        saw Mordecai in the king\u2019s gate, that he neither rose nor trembled before
        him, he was filled with wrath against Mordecai. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Nevertheless, Haman restrained himself and went home, and he sent
        and brought his friends and his wife Zeresh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Haman recounted to them the splendor of his riches, the number
        of his sons, all the promotions with which the king had honored him, and
        how he had advanced him above the officials and the servants of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Haman said, \u201CEven Queen Esther let no one but me come with
        the king to the feast she prepared. And tomorrow also I am invited by her
        together with the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yet all this is worth nothing to me, so long as I see Mordecai the
        Jew sitting at the king\u2019s gate.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then his wife Zeresh and all his friends said to him, \u201CLet a
        gallows[[COMMENT(0)]] fifty cubits high be made, and in the morning tell
        the king to have Mordecai hanged upon it. Then go joyfully with the king
        to the feast.\u201D This idea pleased Haman, and he had the gallows made."
      comments:
      - number: '5:14 '
        content: Or ; twice in this verse (see note on 2:23)A was about 18 inches
          or 45 centimeters
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The King Honors Mordecai'
      title: The King Honors Mordecai
      number: 1
      content: '  On that night the king could not sleep. And he gave orders to bring
        the book of memorable deeds, the chronicles, and they were read before the
        king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And it was found written how Mordecai had told about Bigthana[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and Teresh, two of the king\u2019s eunuchs, who guarded the threshold, and
        who had sought to lay hands on King Ahasuerus. "
      comments:
      - number: '6:2 '
        content: is an alternate spelling of (see 2:21)
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the king said, \u201CWhat honor or distinction has been bestowed
        on Mordecai for this?\u201D The king\u2019s young men who attended him said,
        \u201CNothing has been done for him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the king said, \u201CWho is in the court?\u201D Now Haman had
        just entered the outer court of the king\u2019s palace to speak to the king
        about having Mordecai hanged on the gallows[[COMMENT(0)]] that he had prepared
        for him. "
      comments:
      - number: '6:4 '
        content: Or (see note on 2:23)
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the king\u2019s young men told him, \u201CHaman is there, standing
        in the court.\u201D And the king said, \u201CLet him come in.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Haman came in, and the king said to him, \u201CWhat should be
        done to the man whom the king delights to honor?\u201D And Haman said to
        himself, \u201CWhom would the king delight to honor more than me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Haman said to the king, \u201CFor the man whom the king delights
        to honor, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'let royal robes be brought, which the king has worn, and the horse
        that the king has ridden, and on whose head a royal crown[[COMMENT(0)]] is
        set. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And let the robes and the horse be handed over to one of the king\u2019s
        most noble officials. Let them dress the man whom the king delights to honor,
        and let them lead him on the horse through the square of the city, proclaiming
        before him: \u2018Thus shall it be done to the man whom the king delights
        to honor.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the king said to Haman, \u201CHurry; take the robes and the
        horse, as you have said, and do so to Mordecai the Jew, who sits at the king\u2019s
        gate. Leave out nothing that you have mentioned.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Haman took the robes and the horse, and he dressed Mordecai and
        led him through the square of the city, proclaiming before him, \u201CThus
        shall it be done to the man whom the king delights to honor.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Mordecai returned to the king\u2019s gate. But Haman hurried
        to his house, mourning and with his head covered. "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Esther Reveals Haman\u2019s Plot"
      title: "Esther Reveals Haman\u2019s Plot"
      number: 13
      content: "And Haman told his wife Zeresh and all his friends everything that
        had happened to him. Then his wise men and his wife Zeresh said to him, \u201CIf
        Mordecai, before whom you have begun to fall, is of the Jewish people, you
        will not overcome him but will surely fall before him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "While they were yet talking with him, the king\u2019s eunuchs arrived
        and hurried to bring Haman to the feast that Esther had prepared."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  So the king and Haman went in to feast with Queen Esther. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And on the second day, as they were drinking wine after the feast,
        the king again said to Esther, \u201CWhat is your wish, Queen Esther? It
        shall be granted you. And what is your request? Even to the half of my kingdom,
        it shall be fulfilled.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Queen Esther answered, \u201CIf I have found favor in your sight,
        O king, and if it please the king, let my life be granted me for my wish,
        and my people for my request. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For we have been sold, I and my people, to be destroyed, to be killed,
        and to be annihilated. If we had been sold merely as slaves, men and women,
        I would have been silent, for our affliction is not to be compared with the
        loss to the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then King Ahasuerus said to Queen Esther, \u201CWho is he, and where
        is he, who has dared[[COMMENT(0)]] to do this?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '7:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: Haman Is Hanged'
      title: Haman Is Hanged
      number: 6
      content: "And Esther said, \u201CA foe and enemy! This wicked Haman!\u201D
        Then Haman was terrified before the king and the queen.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the king arose in his wrath from the wine-drinking and went into
        the palace garden, but Haman stayed to beg for his life from Queen Esther,
        for he saw that harm was determined against him by the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the king returned from the palace garden to the place where they
        were drinking wine, as Haman was falling on the couch where Esther was. And
        the king said, \u201CWill he even assault the queen in my presence, in my
        own house?\u201D As the word left the mouth of the king, they covered Haman\u2019s
        face. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Harbona, one of the eunuchs in attendance on the king, said,
        \u201CMoreover, the gallows[[COMMENT(0)]] that Haman has prepared for Mordecai,
        whose word saved the king, is standing at Haman\u2019s house, fifty cubits
        high.\u201D And the king said, \u201CHang him on that.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '7:9 '
        content: Or ; also verse 10 (see note on 2:23)A was about 18 inches or 45
          centimeters
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: So they hanged Haman on the gallows that he had prepared for Mordecai.
        Then the wrath of the king abated.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Esther Saves the Jews'
      title: Esther Saves the Jews
      number: 1
      content: '  On that day King Ahasuerus gave to Queen Esther the house of Haman,
        the enemy of the Jews. And Mordecai came before the king, for Esther had
        told what he was to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the king took off his signet ring, which he had taken from Haman,
        and gave it to Mordecai. And Esther set Mordecai over the house of Haman.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Esther spoke again to the king. She fell at his feet and wept
        and pleaded with him to avert the evil plan of Haman the Agagite and the
        plot that he had devised against the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When the king held out the golden scepter to Esther, Esther rose
        and stood before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And she said, \u201CIf it please the king, and if I have found favor
        in his sight, and if the thing seems right before the king, and I am pleasing
        in his eyes, let an order be written to revoke the letters devised by Haman
        the Agagite, the son of Hammedatha, which he wrote to destroy the Jews who
        are in all the provinces of the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For how can I bear to see the calamity that is coming to my people?
        Or how can I bear to see the destruction of my kindred?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then King Ahasuerus said to Queen Esther and to Mordecai the Jew,
        \u201CBehold, I have given Esther the house of Haman, and they have hanged
        him on the gallows,[[COMMENT(0)]] because he intended to lay hands on the
        Jews. "
      comments:
      - number: '8:7 '
        content: Or (see note on 2:23)
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But you may write as you please with regard to the Jews, in the name
        of the king, and seal it with the king\u2019s ring, for an edict written
        in the name of the king and sealed with the king\u2019s ring cannot be revoked.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  The king\u2019s scribes were summoned at that time, in the third
        month, which is the month of Sivan, on the twenty-third day. And an edict
        was written, according to all that Mordecai commanded concerning the Jews,
        to the satraps and the governors and the officials of the provinces from
        India to Ethiopia, 127 provinces, to each province in its own script and
        to each people in its own language, and also to the Jews in their script
        and their language. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And he wrote in the name of King Ahasuerus and sealed it with the
        king\u2019s signet ring. Then he sent the letters by mounted couriers riding
        on swift horses that were used in the king\u2019s service, bred from the
        royal stud, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'saying that the king allowed the Jews who were in every city to gather
        and defend their lives, to destroy, to kill, and to annihilate any armed
        force of any people or province that might attack them, children and women
        included, and to plunder their goods, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'on one day throughout all the provinces of King Ahasuerus, on the
        thirteenth day of the twelfth month, which is the month of Adar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'A copy of what was written was to be issued as a decree in every
        province, being publicly displayed to all peoples, and the Jews were to be
        ready on that day to take vengeance on their enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So the couriers, mounted on their swift horses that were used in
        the king\u2019s service, rode out hurriedly, urged by the king\u2019s command.
        And the decree was issued in Susa the citadel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Mordecai went out from the presence of the king in royal robes
        of blue and white, with a great golden crown[[COMMENT(0)]] and a robe of
        fine linen and purple, and the city of Susa shouted and rejoiced. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:15 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The Jews had light and gladness and joy and honor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And in every province and in every city, wherever the king\u2019s
        command and his edict reached, there was gladness and joy among the Jews,
        a feast and a holiday. And many from the peoples of the country declared
        themselves Jews, for fear of the Jews had fallen on them."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Jews Destroy Their Enemies'
      title: The Jews Destroy Their Enemies
      number: 1
      content: "    Now in the twelfth month, which is the month of Adar, on the
        thirteenth day of the same, when the king\u2019s command and edict were about
        to be carried out, on the very day when the enemies of the Jews hoped to
        gain the mastery over them, the reverse occurred: the Jews gained mastery
        over those who hated them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Jews gathered in their cities throughout all the provinces of
        King Ahasuerus to lay hands on those who sought their harm. And no one could
        stand against them, for the fear of them had fallen on all peoples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All the officials of the provinces and the satraps and the governors
        and the royal agents also helped the Jews, for the fear of Mordecai had fallen
        on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For Mordecai was great in the king\u2019s house, and his fame spread
        throughout all the provinces, for the man Mordecai grew more and more powerful. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Jews struck all their enemies with the sword, killing and destroying
        them, and did as they pleased to those who hated them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In Susa the citadel itself the Jews killed and destroyed 500 men, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and also killed Parshandatha and Dalphon and Aspatha '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and Poratha and Adalia and Aridatha '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and Parmashta and Arisai and Aridai and Vaizatha, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the ten sons of Haman the son of Hammedatha, the enemy of the Jews,
        but they laid no hand on the plunder.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'That very day the number of those killed in Susa the citadel was
        reported to the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the king said to Queen Esther, \u201CIn Susa the citadel the
        Jews have killed and destroyed 500 men and also the ten sons of Haman. What
        then have they done in the rest of the king\u2019s provinces! Now what is
        your wish? It shall be granted you. And what further is your request? It
        shall be fulfilled.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Esther said, \u201CIf it please the king, let the Jews who are
        in Susa be allowed tomorrow also to do according to this day\u2019s edict.
        And let the ten sons of Haman be hanged on the gallows.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:13 '
        content: Or ; also verse 25 (see note on 2:23)
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the king commanded this to be done. A decree was issued in Susa,
        and the ten sons of Haman were hanged. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The Jews who were in Susa gathered also on the fourteenth day of
        the month of Adar and they killed 300 men in Susa, but they laid no hands
        on the plunder.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  Now the rest of the Jews who were in the king\u2019s provinces
        also gathered to defend their lives, and got relief from their enemies and
        killed 75,000 of those who hated them, but they laid no hands on the plunder. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'This was on the thirteenth day of the month of Adar, and on the fourteenth
        day they rested and made that a day of feasting and gladness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But the Jews who were in Susa gathered on the thirteenth day and
        on the fourteenth, and rested on the fifteenth day, making that a day of
        feasting and gladness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Feast of Purim Inaugurated'
      title: The Feast of Purim Inaugurated
      number: 19
      content: 'Therefore the Jews of the villages, who live in the rural towns,
        hold the fourteenth day of the month of Adar as a day for gladness and feasting,
        as a holiday, and as a day on which they send gifts of food to one another.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Mordecai recorded these things and sent letters to all the Jews
        who were in all the provinces of King Ahasuerus, both near and far, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'obliging them to keep the fourteenth day of the month Adar and also
        the fifteenth day of the same, year by year, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'as the days on which the Jews got relief from their enemies, and
        as the month that had been turned for them from sorrow into gladness and
        from mourning into a holiday; that they should make them days of feasting
        and gladness, days for sending gifts of food to one another and gifts to
        the poor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So the Jews accepted what they had started to do, and what Mordecai
        had written to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For Haman the Agagite, the son of Hammedatha, the enemy of all the
        Jews, had plotted against the Jews to destroy them, and had cast Pur (that
        is, cast lots), to crush and to destroy them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But when it came before the king, he gave orders in writing that
        his evil plan that he had devised against the Jews should return on his own
        head, and that he and his sons should be hanged on the gallows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Therefore they called these days Purim, after the term Pur. Therefore,
        because of all that was written in this letter, and of what they had faced
        in this matter, and of what had happened to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'the Jews firmly obligated themselves and their offspring and all
        who joined them, that without fail they would keep these two days according
        to what was written and at the time appointed every year, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'that these days should be remembered and kept throughout every generation,
        in every clan, province, and city, and that these days of Purim should never
        fall into disuse among the Jews, nor should the commemoration of these days
        cease among their descendants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Queen Esther, the daughter of Abihail, and Mordecai the Jew
        gave full written authority, confirming this second letter about Purim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Letters were sent to all the Jews, to the 127 provinces of the kingdom
        of Ahasuerus, in words of peace and truth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'that these days of Purim should be observed at their appointed seasons,
        as Mordecai the Jew and Queen Esther obligated them, and as they had obligated
        themselves and their offspring, with regard to their fasts and their lamenting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: The command of Esther confirmed these practices of Purim, and it was
        recorded in writing.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Greatness of Mordecai'
      title: The Greatness of Mordecai
      number: 1
      content: '  King Ahasuerus imposed tax on the land and on the coastlands of
        the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And all the acts of his power and might, and the full account of
        the high honor of Mordecai, to which the king advanced him, are they not
        written in the Book of the Chronicles of the kings of Media and Persia? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For Mordecai the Jew was second in rank to King Ahasuerus, and he
        was great among the Jews and popular with the multitude of his brothers,
        for he sought the welfare of his people and spoke peace to all his people.
      comments: []
